"title": "6027: sin, God's remedy for",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6027",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Under the old covenant, sin was forgiven through sacrifice, prefiguring the atoning death of Jesus Christ, which brings forgiveness of sins under the new covenant.</p>\n<h2>Atonement for sins in the OT was through the shedding of blood</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:11\">LEV 17:11</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Kinds of sin offering in the OT</h2>\n<h3>The sin offering was for unintentional sins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:1-Lev5:13\">LEV 4:1–5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:22-Num15:31\">NUM 15:22–15:31</a></p>\n<h3>The guilt offering was for unintentional sins, where restitution was required</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:14-Lev6:7\">LEV 5:14–6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:5-Num5:10\">NUM 5:5–5:10</a></p>\n<h3>The annual Day of Atonement cleansed the nation of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:1-Lev16:34\">LEV 16:1–16:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:11-Exod30:16\">EXO 30:11–30:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:26-Lev23:32\">LEV 23:26–23:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:7\">HEB 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>The priests made atonement on occasions of deliberate national sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:46-Num16:48\">NUM 16:46–16:48</a> <em>Aaron stops the plague after Korah's sin</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:13\">NUM 25:13</a> <em>Phinehas stops the plague after Moab caused Israel to sin.</em></p>\n<h2>Sacrifices of atonement needed to be accompanied by repentance and a willingness to obey</h2>\n<h3>Worshippers recognised the need for repentance and obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:3\">PRO 21:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:6-Ps40:8\">PSA 40:6–40:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:16-Ps51:17\">PSA 51:16–51:17</a></p>\n<h3>The prophets declared the need for obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:22\">1SA 15:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:11-Isa1:17\">ISA 1:11–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:21-Jer7:23\">JER 7:21–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:6\">HOS 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:6-Mic6:8\">MIC 6:6–6:8</a></p>\n<h3>The prophets warned of judgment to bring people to repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:13\">2KI 17:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:6-Isa31:7\">ISA 31:6–31:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:1-Jer4:4\">JER 4:1–4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:15\">JER 35:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:16-Ezek3:19\">EZK 3:16–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:4-Jonah3:10\">JON 3:4–3:10</a></p>\n<h2>The death of Jesus Christ brings forgiveness for sin</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ died on behalf of sinful humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6\">ROM 5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:26–26:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:13\">JHN 15:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></p>\n<h3>The early church proclaimed that Christ died for the sins of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3\">1CO 15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:25\">ROM 4:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:4\">GAL 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ bore sin on the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10-Isa53:12\">ISA 53:10–53:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ has redeemed people by taking their place</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:6\">1TI 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's death is sacrificial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7\">1CO 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:2\">EPH 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:27\">HEB 7:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:5-Heb10:13\">HEB 10:5–10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:2\">1JN 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:10\">1JN 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>The shedding of Jesus Christ's blood brings forgiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12-Heb9:22\">HEB 9:12–9:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12\">HEB 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14\">REV 7:14</a></p>",
